# 🤖 AutoPilot AI — Complete Project Flow & Architecture

> **Project:** Auto-Responder Digital Twin  
> **Goal:** An AI that reads your WhatsApp messages, decides whether it can confidently reply, auto-sends routine ones, and flags tricky ones for your manual review.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
GPT chatbot/
├── client/                  ← React frontend (Vite)
│   └── src/
│       ├── App.jsx          ← Layout: Sidebar + TopBar + Router
│       ├── main.jsx         ← React entry
│       ├── index.css        ← Full design system (dark theme)
│       ├── pages/
│       │   ├── Dashboard.jsx    ← Stats, Activity, Simulate panel
│       │   ├── Messages.jsx     ← All messages (search/filter)
│       │   ├── ReviewQueue.jsx  ← Approve / Dismiss drafts
│       │   ├── Contacts.jsx     ← VIP contacts + directives
│       │   └── SettingsPage.jsx ← AI config, API keys (UI only)
│       ├── services/
│       │   └── api.js           ← All HTTP calls to backend
│       └── hooks/
│           └── useLiveData.js   ← Auto-polling custom hook
│
├── server/                  ← Node.js + Express backend
│   ├── index.js             ← Server entry, middleware, routes
│   ├── store.js             ← In-memory "database"
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── webhook.js       ← POST /webhook/whatsapp (Twilio)
│   │   ├── simulate.js      ← POST /api/simulate (dev testing)
│   │   ├── review.js        ← Approve / Dismiss queue items
│   │   ├── messages.js      ← GET messages, stats, activity
│   │   └── contacts.js      ← CRUD for VIP contacts
│   ├── services/
│   │   ├── openai.js        ← GPT-4o-mini: draft + confidence
│   │   └── twilio.js        ← Send WhatsApp replies
│   ├── .env                 ← Your actual keys (gitignored)
│   └── .env.example         ← Template for keys
│
└── tech_and_features.md     ← Feature spec document
```

