## 🔄 End-to-End Message Flow

This is the **core loop** of the entire application:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["📩 Incoming WhatsApp Message"] --> B["Twilio forwards to POST /webhook/whatsapp"]
    B --> C["Find contact directive from VIP list"]
    C --> D["Call OpenAI: analyzeAndDraft()"]
    D --> E{"Confidence >= 85%\nor autoApprove?"}
    E -- "Yes" --> F["✅ Auto-send reply via Twilio"]
    E -- "No" --> G["⌛ Add to Review Queue"]
    F --> H["Update stats + log activity"]
    G --> H
    H --> I["Frontend polls & displays results"]
    I --> J{"User reviews flagged message"}
    J -- "Approve" --> K["Send via Twilio + remove from queue"]
    J -- "Dismiss" --> L["Mark dismissed + remove from queue"]
```

### Step-by-step breakdown:

| Step | What happens | File |
|------|-------------|------|
| **1. Message arrives** | Twilio receives a WhatsApp message to your number and sends a webhook POST to your server | [webhook.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/routes/webhook.js) |
| **2. Contact lookup** | Server checks if the sender's phone matches any VIP contact with custom directives (e.g. "Mom → always be warm") | [store.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/store.js#L90-L101) |
| **3. AI Analysis** | OpenAI GPT-4o-mini receives the message + persona rules + contact directive → returns a JSON with `draft`, `confidence`, `sentiment`, `intent` | [openai.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/services/openai.js) |
| **4. Confidence decision** | If `confidence >= 85` (or contact has `autoApprove: true`) → auto-send. Otherwise → queue for review | [webhook.js:68](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/routes/webhook.js#L68) |
| **5. Auto-send** | [sendWhatsApp()](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/services/twilio.js#24-52) fires the reply through Twilio | [twilio.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/services/twilio.js) |
| **6. Review queue** | Low-confidence messages are stored with draft + reason. Dashboard shows them for approval | [review.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/routes/review.js) |
| **7. Dashboard polls** | Frontend polls every 4 seconds for stats, messages, and activity | [useLiveData.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/hooks/useLiveData.js) |

---

## 🧠 AI Engine (OpenAI Service)

[openai.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/services/openai.js)

### What it does:
1. Constructs a **system prompt** with Aditya's persona rules + contact-specific directive
2. Sends the incoming message to **GPT-4o-mini**
3. Returns structured JSON: `{ draft, confidence, sentiment, intent }`

### Persona Rules (hardcoded in store):
- Short, punchy, real replies — no formal letter vibes
- Uses 'bro', 'dude', 'yaar' with friends
- Professional with clients, warm with family
- Never says "I apologize" or "I am an AI"

### Confidence Scoring Guide:
| Range | Level | Examples |
|-------|-------|---------|
| 90-100 | ✅ Routine | Greetings, birthday wishes, simple Q&A |
| 70-89 | 🟡 Moderate | Scheduling, social plans, friend chat |
| 40-69 | 🟠 Higher stakes | Work/client messages, commitments |
| 0-39 | 🔴 Sensitive | Emotional conflicts, financial, emergencies |

### Demo Mode:
When no OpenAI API key is present, the service falls back to **mock responses** (keyword matching):
- "time" / "meeting" → 97% confidence auto-reply
- "project" / "update" → 58% confidence → goes to review
- "upset" / "angry" → 38% confidence → goes to review

