## 🖥️ Frontend Pages

### 1. Dashboard ([Dashboard.jsx](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx))
- **Mode Banner** — Shows "Live" or "Demo Mode" based on API key status
- **4 Stat Cards** — Total Replied, Auto-Sent, Needs Review, Total Messages
- **Recent Messages** — Last few messages with confidence bars and status badges
- **Live Activity Feed** — Real-time log of what the AI did (auto-sent, flagged, etc.)
- **AI Engine Status** — Persona Match Accuracy, Auto-Reply Rate, Sentiment Detection bars
- **Simulate Panel** — Type a fake incoming message → see the AI's draft + confidence + decision

### 2. All Messages ([Messages.jsx](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/pages/Messages.jsx))
- Search by sender name or message text
- Filter by platform (WhatsApp / Instagram / Facebook)
- Filter by status (Auto-Sent / Review / Dismissed)
- Shows draft, confidence %, intent badge for each message

### 3. Review Queue ([ReviewQueue.jsx](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/pages/ReviewQueue.jsx))
- Shows all messages where AI confidence was too low
- Each item shows: original message, AI draft, confidence, sentiment, intent, reason
- Two actions: **Approve** (optionally edit the draft) or **Dismiss**
- Approving sends the reply via Twilio

### 4. VIP Contacts ([Contacts.jsx](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/pages/Contacts.jsx))
- Add/Edit/Delete contacts with custom directives
- Set tags (Family, Friends, Work, General)
- Toggle `autoApprove` — skip review for trusted contacts
- Edit the AI directive per contact (e.g. "Always be warm and loving")

### 5. Settings ([SettingsPage.jsx](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/client/src/pages/SettingsPage.jsx))
- Confidence threshold slider (50-99%)
- Active persona selector
- Platform connection toggles (WhatsApp connected, IG/FB future)
- Notification & DND toggles
- API key input fields

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Settings page is UI-only right now** — the toggles and inputs don't actually save to the backend. The confidence threshold is read from the server's [.env](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/.env) file, not from the frontend.

---

## 💾 Data Layer (In-Memory Store)

[store.js](file:///E:/ANTIGRAVITY/Projects/GPT%20chatbot/server/store.js)

All data lives in a JavaScript object in memory. **No database yet** — restarting the server clears everything.

| Collection | Purpose | Cap |
|-----------|---------|-----|
| `messages[]` | All processed messages | 200 max |
| `reviewQueue[]` | Messages needing manual approval | Uncapped |
| `contacts[]` | VIP contact directives | Seeded with "Mom" + "Default" |
| `persona[]` | Aditya's writing style rules | 6 rules |
| `activity[]` | Event log (auto-sent, flagged, approved) | 50 max |
| `stats{}` | Counters: totalReplied, autoSent, needsReview | — |

---

## 🔌 External Services

| Service | Purpose | Current Status |
|---------|---------|----------------|
| **OpenAI** (GPT-4o-mini) | Generates reply drafts + confidence scores | Works live with key, falls back to mock without |
| **Twilio** (WhatsApp API) | Sends WhatsApp messages | Works live with credentials, logs to console without |

Both services have a **demo mode** — the app is fully usable for testing without any API keys.

